FBIS4-39008 "drsov108_b_94022" FBIS-SOV-94-108 Daily Report 3 Jun 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military Issues Joint Exercises in Sea of Okhotsk Begin 5 Jun Joint Exercises in Sea of Okhotsk Begin 5 Jun LD0306174894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1603 GMT 3 Jun 94 LD0306174894 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] A joint exercise of ships and aircraft of the Russian Navy and border forces will take place in the central area of the Sea of Okhotsk from June 5 to 25. The exercise will concentrate on the defense of marine communication and on rocket and artillery fire. Interfax has learned that the scenarios will also include rocket and torpedo attacks from submarines, ships and aircraft and rebuffing an enemy with convoy defenses.
